<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>PS00042</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : IMPROPER IMPLEMENTATION OF THE EMISSION TESTING PROVISION OF THE PHILIPPINE CLEAN AIR ACT OF 1999</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Emission Testing</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Rep. Abayon spoke on the issue of the improper
implementation of the emission testing provision of the Philippine Clean Air Act of 1999. He relayed the concern of one of his constituents regarding emission testing and inquired into the status of emission testing centers as he lamented that there are certain unscrupulous individuals who are taking advantage of the situation for their personal gain. As such, he urged the Departments of Trade and Industry (DTI), and
Transportation (DOTr) to review the accreditation of the authorized emission testing centers.
INTERPELLATION OF REP. SANDOVAL
Rep. Sandoval agreed with the concerns raised by
Rep. Abayon and likewise disclosed that fake
apprehending officers who are not connected with the Land Transportation Office (LTO) are rampant along Epifanio delos Santos Avenue (EDSA) and prey on unsuspecting motorists. They also dwelled on the issue of unscrupulous emission testing operators who allow emission testing of vehicles in absentia but are still given permits to operate by the LTO; the endless approval of permits to operate private emission testing centers; and the need for the LTO and the DOTr to review the system of emission testing. 
(SOURCE: House Journal No.11,pp.17&18)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ABAYON, HARLIN NEIL III J.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-08-16</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Speech-Privilege Hour</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REMARKS:&nbspInterpellation by Rep. Sandoval</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECOLOGY ON 2016-09-06</td></tr></table>